Leszno  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Barczewo, within Olsztyn County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-east of Barczewo and  east of the regional capital Olsztyn. It is located in Warmia.
In the past, the village was also called Leszno Wielkie to distinguish it from the nearby settlement of Leszno Ma≈Çe. In 1857, it had a population of 168.
